text.p: These are the leading stories in the Maltese press on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

- Prime Minister Eddie Fenech Adami keeps electorate guessing over election date. Malta rife with rumours of an impending election but Adami told radio station on Sunday he saw no reason why the budget should not be presented as usual in November. Elections must be held by June.
- Prime Minister Adami says Nationalist Party electoral programme will show party's vision for the future.
- Tug Malta firm buys tug boat secondhand from Japan, modified in Japanese shipyard.
- George Vella, acting leader of Malta Labour Party, promises transparency if the MLP is elected to government.
- Labour leader Alfred Sant returns from United States after attending Socialist International meeting.
